summary: Jitesh calls the customer care of a noodle company to register a complaint about a purchased product but the call is transferred to another department because of technical problems. Jitesh is asked to provide the address where he purchased the noodles, the shop's name, the shop's address, and the batch number of the product. He is then asked to provide the manufacturing date, the pack's weight, and the expiry date. Jitesh is told that the shopkeeper will be contacted to resolve the issue. However, due to some miscommunication, Jitesh is provided with another shop's information. He is then asked to provide his whatsapp number so that the correct information can be shared, but there are further technical issues. Jitesh is frustrated and decides to hang up the call.

Jitesh tells him that it will take some time to resolve his issue and will inform him once it is done. He also takes down Vishal Ji's WhatsApp number and tells him that he will be contacted soon.
